FBIS3-41123 "jptdd005__l94060" JPRS-TDD-94-005-L Document Type:JPRS Document Title:Narcotics 1 February 1994 EAST EUROPE BULGARIA Svilengrad Court Sentences Macedonian, Polish Heroin Smugglers AU2701131994 Sofia BTA in English 2121 GMT 26 Jan 94 AU2701131994 Sofia BTA Language: English Article Type:BFN ["Today"--BTA lead] [Excerpt] Sofia, January 26 (BTA) -- The Svilengrad District Court sentenced Erfan Erfi of Macedonia to three years and eight months imprisonment for attempting to smuggle 10.230 kg of unrefined heroin in an Opel Manta on September 4, 1993. Jaroslaw Nedzulka, a Polish national caught in an attempt to carry 10.430 kg of heroin illegally across the border in an Audi, received a six year prison sentence. Andrzej Dromond, who travelled together with Nedzulka, was acquitted. The drug traffickers will also pay fines, and their cars are confiscated.
